Story Title: As a developer, I want our code to be well documented so that it is readable.
As a developer, I want to create the API so that has the correct endpoints so that we can utilize it in our website.
As a developer, I want to have links to instances of a certain model so that it all links together.
As a developer, I want instances of my model in my website to be rich with different content so that it is readable and fluid.
As a developer, I want my information from the backend flowing to the front end.
As a developer, I want my database to be fully connected. As a result, we need to change the GAME ids to match the other tables.
As a developer, I want to change the styling to SCSS so that it looks nicer.
As a developer, I want to utilize Trello so that it contains the progress of our project in order to keep track of what needs to be done and what is currently done.
As a developer, I want to change the frontend so that it is implemented with Flask and React so that we can include filtering, pagination, and sorting.
As a developer, I want to implement the RestFul API so that it is implemented using SQLAlchemy and a SQL database so that we can get information from both.
As a developer, I want to change the frontend so that it is implemented with Flask and React so that we can route the dynamic pages properly.
As a developer, I want to change the frontend so that it is implemented with Flask and React so that we can update the information on the about page to display the correct information.
As a developer, I want to change the frontend so that it is implemented with Flask and React so that we can create a 404 page.
As a developer, I want to make a set of Unit tests so that it is implemented with Postman so that we can do tests and debug.
As a developer, I want to create a UML diagram so that it shows the communication with its users.
As a developer, I want to change the technical report so that it contains information about the databases so that other software developers understand what is going on.
As a developer, I want to change the frontend so that it is connected to our API so that information can be taken from our API.
As a developer, I want to change the frontend so that it is implemented with Flask and React so that we can generate pages dynamically.
As a developer, I want to change the frontend so that it is styled with CSS framework so that it looks nice.
As a developer, I want to change the frontend so that it is implemented with Flask and React so that we can create dynamic pages for each individual model.
As a user, if my search keywords return more than 10 results, I would like to see the search results be paginated (Total # of search results / 10 = total # of pages)
As a user, I would like to be able to click on valid search results returned by my search keywords
As a developer, I would like to have the EsportGuru's API (api.esportguru.com) to conform to its respective API document at (https://thienmint.docs.apiary.io/)
As a developer, I would like to have robust unit tests for all user-defined functions in models.py
As a user, if my search keywords are not found in any of the models, I would like to be informed of that.
As a developer, I would like to be able to send a search query and get back a JSON with the search results categorized by each of the models.
As a user, I would like to see all instantaces of each model that exceed a certain threshold be paginated (Total # of instances / threshold = # of pages)
As a user, I would like to be able to search the entire website with some keywords and get back a search result page with found keywords highlighted
As a user, I would like to be able to filter through each of the model (Player, Game, Tournament, Team) by some features (i.e name, date, ...)
As a user, I would like to be able to sort each of the model (Player, Game, Tournament, Team) by some features (i.e. name, date, ...)
